  <a href="#1" id="1">
   On Easter Sunday, three Cabinet ministers supported John Major in the wake of speculation
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   that he could be forced out this autumn.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Both Secretary of State for Education John Patten and Michael Howard, the Home Secretary, dismissed talk of a leadership contest before the next general election.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Lord Wakeham, Leader of the House of Lords, called on Torries
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   to be loyal to Mr. Major.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   One poll shows
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   that Michael Heseltine is the favorite
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   to replace Mr. Major
  </a>
  <a href="#9" id="9">
   if he is forced out,
  </a>
  <a href="#10" id="10">
   but that Michael Portillo will vigorously campaign to secure Eurosceptic policies from the eventual winner.
  </a>
